				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Lady Vox .. doable with 1 grp?<a name="37123"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Apr 28 04 5:39 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>Vox and Naggy are certainly 1 groupable, and not with elemental geared/millions of AAed, sacced 65s down to 52. That is just silly, nobody would do that. Bazaar level gear is AMAZING compared to the gear that was originally intended for level 50s raiding vox/naggy. 
<br />

<br />
A few people in my guild, which is nowhere near elementals(when we did vox/naggy regularly last summer some of us didn't even have the PoJ trials done), decided to try it for a couple bards(one of them my alt). Our first few attempts we struggled quite a bit getting the strategy down, and had 2 bards, a monk, a shaman, and 3 clerics(all botted). 
<br />

<br />
First of all, don't charge into the dragon's lair with all your &quot;raid&quot;. Toss a heal over time on your tank, and have him/her pull the dragon back to the door. Then push vox into the wall that your clerics are hiding behind, to make sure you don't get out of range of heals. The healers can stay outside the lair to heal, and have no AE to deal with. Second, buff order is important. We always did 4 junk buffs, then had good buffs after that, with virtue, seasons, focus, and magic resists being at the very bottom. We did have a level 65 cleric, shammy, chanter, and druid to buff, they were the mains of the lvl 52s. Even if you can't get 65 buffs, you should have those types of buffs at the very bottom. I would say a bard is necessary for this for 2 reasons. What you really need is a good drum, and Singing Steel Boots. I twisted the low level fire/cold/magic resist song, the low level magic resist song(sorry can't remember the names now), and a cast of singing steel boots. Because the group constantly got a fresh levitation, in all our tries, we never lost any of our key buffs. In fact, I rarely lost all 4 of my junk buffs. Also, with the resist buffs/songs, we got feared a grand total of 0 times, and full resists of the damage AE were fairly common. We all had low to mid 200 magic resist to do that. With that being the case, the clerics just had to keep our tank alive(tossing heals to the others in the group taking minimal damage from the AEs).
<br />

<br />
We killed vox and naggy about 2 dozen times before finally getting 2 scales. The other bard got her scales and leveled up quickly, and the shaman stopped coming. We did it a couple times with 3 clerics, monk, and my bard, although we lost about 50% of the time with those 5. Then a warrior joined us and it became laughably easy with 3 clerics, monk, warrior, bard. Our only losses were our first few tries, or when we tried with too few clerics. Three clerics seemed to be the magic number. Sure, we had a perfect combination of classes with our alts, and up and coming guild members, and everyone might not be able to do that, but its doable with a far from uber group, if you know what you are doing. Btw, the fights always took about 5 minutes, which is somewhat good since vox never once CHed herself, I am guessing because she was OOM.
<br />

<br />
p.s. multiple times people watched us. They laughed at us at first when they saw our force, then were amazed and asked for our tactics after we won. Above is pretty much all we did. Its not that complicated. We are all too high to do them now, so keeping the secret does us no good anymore. <img src="/skins/default/images/emotions/emotion-1.gif" border="0" alt="Smiley" hspace="2" /> </span></td>
